@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "HomeServer";
}

<style>
    .right-link {
        text-align: right; /* Aligns the link to the right of its column */
    }

    .container{
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    .appList ul {
        font-family: 'Poppins', Verdana, sans-serif;
        font-size: 20px;
        list-style-type: none; /* Remove default bullets */
        text-align: left; /* Align text to the left, not center */
        margin-left: 0; /* Remove default margin */
        padding-left: 0; /* Remove default padding for accurate positioning */
    }

        .appList ul li {
            position: relative; /* Position relative for absolute positioning of pseudo-element */
            padding-left: 30px; /* Space for bullet */
        }

            .appList ul li::before {
                content: "•"; /* Unicode character for bullet */
                color: #ccc; /* Light color for standard mode */
                position: absolute; /* Absolute positioning of the bullet */
                left: 0; /* Position at the start of the item */
                top: 0; /* Align with the top of the line */
                font-size: 20px; /* Ensures the bullet is the same size as the text */
            }
</style>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col-2">
            <a href="https://github.com/NinePiece2/TrueNASHomeServer" target="_blank" class="d-block">GitHub</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-8 text-center">
            <h1>Home Server</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="col-2 right-link">
            <!-- Empty column to maintain center alignment -->
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="container">
    <p>This project details the TrueNAS Home server I developed, marking my entry into home labbing. Building this server has enabled me to host a variety of additional projects independently, enhancing my hands-on experience and technical expertise in managing and deploying server-based applications including:</p>
    <br />
    <div class="row " style="margin-left: 20%;">
        <div class="col-auto">
            <div class="appList">
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li>Microsoft SQL Server</li>
                    <li>Kemp Load Balancer</li>
                    <li>Kubernetes</li>
                    <li>Proxmox</li>
                    <li>Home Assistant</li>
                    <li>Pi-Hole</li>
                    <li>Wireguard VPS</li>
                    <li>Internet Information Services Host</li>
                    <li>GitHub Self-Hosted Runners</li>
                    <li>Plex Media Server</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
